Bubble Sort: A sorting algorithm where the largest values bubble up to the
top.

Compares two values, if the second is larger than the first, we swap till
we reach the end of the array, we repeat the process till we can no longer
swap

---

Before we sort, we must swap!

Many sorting algorithms involve some type of swapping functionality
(e.g. swapping two numbers to put them in order)
// ES5
function swap(arr, idx1, idx2) {
    var temp = arr[idx1]
    arr[idx1] = arr[idx2]
    arr[idx2] = arr[idx1]
}

// ES6
const wap = (arr, idx1, idx2) => {
    [arr[idx1], arr[idx1]] = [arr[idx2], arr[idx1]]
}

---

Time complexity: O(n^2)